title: New Arrivals Mission Incident Action Plan

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Please provide the most up-to-date version of the New Arrivals Mission Incident Action Plan.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Forest Gregg

title: Medical Request Form (Office of Emergency Management and Communications)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Please provide records sufficient to show the number of submitted Medical Request Form Forms (https://app.smartsheet.com/b/form/ce71b30ce7ef4ed0ac5b27cababb7f6f) per week and district and type of request (Shelter Placement, Isolation Needed, Appointment needed, Medical Follow up). 

If this would require the construction of a new record, and the agency is unwilling to do so, please provide  an export of SmartSheet records with all but the submission date, district, and Type of Request fields redacted.

Please provide records for all form submittals. If providing all records would be unduly burdensome, please provide all submittals received from August 1, 2023 to present.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Forest Gregg

title: Healthcare intake form (Office of Emergency Management and Communications)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Please provide records sufficient to show the number of submitted Healthcare Mutual Aid Intake Forms (https://airtable.com/app6OFW7y6kWIKDk4/shri9icgOqRW54WSt) per week and submitted location. In the per week, per location tabulations, please include a tabulation showing the number of records that indicate whether the following fields were selected: "Pregnant Mom," "Infant or Child under 5 years old," "Diabetic," "Hypertension."

If this would require the construction of a new record, and the agency is unwilling to do so, please provide  an export of Air Table records with all but the submission date, submitted location,  "Pregnant Mom," "Infant or Child under 5 years old," "Diabetic," and "Hypertension" fields redacted.

Please provide records for all form submittals. If providing all records would be unduly burdensome, please provide all submittals received from August 1, 2023 to present.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Forest Gregg
